domain_key|pattern_key|narrowing_key|priority|narrowing_title|narrowing_text|missing_range_signal_key|status|lookup_key
leadership-approach|vision_results_process_people|narrowing_1|1|When the frame stays above the work|Vision can narrow when the future frame keeps expanding before the current work has a clear decision, method, or people grounding. The work may sound coherent, but people may still be unsure what changes next.|people|active|leadership-approach::vision_results_process_people::narrowing_1
leadership-approach|vision_results_process_people|narrowing_2|2|When Vision and Results take most of the space|Vision and Results can narrow together when the combination of direction, meaning, and future consequence with decision, ownership, and follow-through answers the first questions too quickly. The pattern may look productive, but it can leave less room for clearer sequence, standards, or handover or clearer communication, inclusion, and relational judgement until the work is harder to adjust.|process|active|leadership-approach::vision_results_process_people::narrowing_2
leadership-approach|vision_results_process_people|narrowing_3|3|Before People is added|Process can add range before People is brought in deliberately, but the pattern may still narrow if People is left until later. The likely miss is progress that looks organised from the outside while commitment, confidence, or shared understanding needs more attention, especially when Vision and Results already feel convincing.|people|active|leadership-approach::vision_results_process_people::narrowing_3
